div.p: The goal of the experimebnt was to soak the crystal of protein kinase CK2 (whise structure, alone and in complex with inhibitors is already known) with ATP, Mg2+ and a peptide substrate. Since the kinetics, at the ionic strength of crystallization, is quite slow, wee hope to cacth the structure of an intermediate of the reaction. For this, three data sets at different timesd (3 min, 5min and 10 min) were measured. I report here only the statistics for the 3 min data set.
